EF means 
 - tool in .net that helps us to work with database using c# code instead of SQL queries.
 - EF automatically converts c# code into SQL queries.
 - EF removes the wiriting SQL queris manually. It allows devlopers to interract with database
   using objects.

Why we use EF
 - Witohut EF write SQL queries manually
 - more chance of error 
 - time consuming.

 + less code 
 + easy to code/develop
 + easy to maintain

without EF 
 - select * from Student where id = 1;
with EF 
 - context.Students.find(1);

EF core 
 - Latest, lightweight and cross platform version
 - EF core is a modern version of EF that works on Windows, Linux and, Mack.

ORM 
 - It maps c# classes to the database tables and object to row.


Coding approch 
 - There are 3 types of coding approch 
    1. Code first approch
     - Start with coding database created automatically.
     - C# classes -> DBContext -> Migration -> Database.

    2. Database first approch
     - Database is already exists gunerate c# classes from DB 

DBContext
  - DBContext is a main class that connects your application to the database
  Ex 
    public DBSet<Student> Students {get; set;}

DBSet 
 - represent table in database.

Migration 
 - Migration is used to create or update the Database structure automatically.


Activity 
 - what is crud operation
 - what is HTTP methods